cyclone.name: ETA
cyclone.current_location: about 250 miles WSW of Grand Cayman
cyclone.trajectory: moving ENE toward the Cayman Islands, forecast to cross central Cuba tonight, reach the Florida Keys/southern Florida Sunday night–Monday, then turn north-northwest into the eastern Gulf of Mexico

weather_observation.watch_coast: Sebastian Inlet southward around the Florida peninsula to Bonita Beach, plus the Florida Keys and Florida Bay
weather_observation.warning_coast: None on Florida east coast (only Cayman Islands, parts of Cuba, NW Bahamas under warning)
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Entire Florida peninsula, Keys, and northward to the Flagler/Volusia County line on the Atlantic side
weather_observation.wind: Gradual increase late Sunday night through Monday with gusts into 40–45 mph range possible
weather_observation.storm_surge: 1–2 ft of inundation possible at high tide along the Space Coast
weather_observation.rainfall: 5–10 inches possible with locally higher amounts, producing flash/urban flooding around Port Canaveral
weather_observation.other_hazards: Dangerous surf and rip currents; isolated tornado risk cannot be ruled out if outer rainbands reach central Florida coast
